+# Gotzportal – standalone copy
+
+This folder is a standalone copy of the gotzportal app (moved out of `goweb`). You can run it on its own.
+
+## First-time setup
+
+```bash
+cd /Users/mdegy/gotzportal
+npm install
+```
+
+**Config:** A `.env.local` is already in place with defaults:
+
+- `ADMIN_PASSWORD=gotzportal-admin-2025` (change in production)
+- `NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000`
+- `POSTGRES_URL=` — **add your Neon connection string** from [console.neon.tech](https://console.neon.tech) to use the database.
+
+All supported variables are listed in `.env.example`. Edit `.env.local` to match your setup.
+
+## Run the app
+
+```bash
+npm run dev
+```
+
+Then open **http://localhost:3000**.
+
+## Git / push
+
+This folder has its own git repo and is connected to:
+
+- **Remote:** `https://github.com/KekeEmmanuel/gotzportal.git`
+- **Branch:** `main`
+
+Use **Source Control** in Cursor (or `git add` / `git commit` / `git push`) from this folder to push changes.
+
+## Useful scripts
+
+- `npm run db:setup` – apply schema to Neon (needs `POSTGRES_URL` in `.env.local`)
+- `npm run db:seed-users` – seed admin user (uses `ADMIN_PASSWORD` from `.env.local`)
